284
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:03,984
Besides, I'm inexperienced.

285
00:17:04,349 --> 00:17:06,134
I can't counter-attack in defense.

286
00:17:07,269 --> 00:17:08,902
So my weakness is...

287
00:17:10,030 --> 00:17:10,927
I'm not powerful enough.

288
00:17:12,022 --> 00:17:13,212
You're not.

289
00:17:14,910 --> 00:17:16,425
But that's not the reason.

290
00:17:17,695 --> 00:17:18,766
You lost to him...

291
00:17:19,464 --> 00:17:21,487
because you changed your fighting tactic.

292
00:17:22,432 --> 00:17:24,519
But my HP was lower.

293
00:17:25,447 --> 00:17:27,002
If I didn't change my tactic...

294
00:17:27,026 --> 00:17:28,922
No tactic is perfect.

295
00:17:30,073 --> 00:17:31,303
The key to winning...

296
00:17:31,930 --> 00:17:33,588
is not what tactic you choose,

297
00:17:34,787 --> 00:17:36,779
but to find one that suits you.

298
00:17:41,255 --> 00:17:44,032
Having too many choices is not as good as having no choice.

299
00:17:47,032 --> 00:17:48,024
Anytime,

300
00:17:48,849 --> 00:17:50,507
You shouldn't easily doubt yourself.

301
00:18:20,431 --> 00:18:23,534
I think sometimes we need to doubt ourselves...

302
00:18:24,375 --> 00:18:26,644
at least on such trifles.

303
00:18:38,626 --> 00:18:41,364
I think Ye Qiu is messing up this time.

304
00:18:42,364 --> 00:18:45,538
It has turned out the mockery they were subjected to is accurate.

305
00:18:45,729 --> 00:18:49,189
They are very weak and vulnerable.

306
00:18:49,213 --> 00:18:49,911
Captain,

307
00:18:50,451 --> 00:18:52,943
you're the only one who lost to them badly.

308
00:18:52,967 --> 00:18:53,967
Nonsense.

309
00:18:54,379 --> 00:18:56,045
